          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Atlanta</placeName>
                                        <date>Apl 21<hi rend="sup">st</hi> 1854</date>.</p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">I received the Box sent<lb/> to my address after
                                        some delay, but up<lb/> to this time I have not distributed
                                        the<lb/> Bibles strictly in accordance with your<lb/>
                                        instructions, as an opportunity offered to<lb/> dispose of
                                        Two. I have taken the liberty of fur=<lb/>=nishing the
                                        parties, and it is likely I shall<lb/> sell one or two
                                        more—at all events the <persName>Revd<lb/> I.
                                                  Shaty<add>?</add></persName> shall be furnished
                                        with his copy,<lb/> as I learn he is about leaving
                                                  <placeName>Augusta</placeName>.<lb/> If <del>it
                                                  be</del> necessary I will advise you of<lb/> more
                                        are required to furnish your subscribers<lb/> through
                                                  me—<persName>Col Mitchell</persName> is absent from<lb/>
                                        <placeName>Athens</placeName>, but I shall send his copy by
                                        the<lb/> first opportunity. I think a <persName>Mr
                                                  <add>?</add></persName><lb/> will take a copy as
                                        soon as he returns<lb/> home, as he has expressed great
                                        anxiety<lb/> to have one, but has been absent since<lb/> I
                                        have been in receipt of them.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed please find check<lb/> on <placeName>New
                                                  York</placeName> for amts collected on yr.<lb/>
                                        account. <persName>A I Brady</persName> Bible $9. subscr $6 $15.<lb/>
                                        <persName>I Mayer</persName> subscript $11.
                                                  <persName>Frankford</persName> $6. 12<lb/>
                                        <persName>Brown</persName>     Do         $6
                                                     <persName>Lazarus</persName>.   $6. 12.<lb/>
                                        <persName>Lazaron</persName> 1 Bible $8. <persName
                                                  role="author">A Alexander</persName> Balance &amp;
                                        Subscription $8. 26<lb/>
                                        <persName role="author">A Alexander</persName> 1 Bible
                                        9<lb/> ½ pr ct premium on check 37 $73.63/100 $74</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p><persName>Mr I. Mayer</persName> has taken a Bible c $9.00<lb/>
                                        which please charge him with, as soon<lb/> as I can sell the
                                        others or collect for you<lb/> a check shall be sent. I wish
                                        it was in my<lb/> power to assist you in your Payments,
                                        but<lb/> times are so dull that it is extremely
                                        diffi<lb/>-cult for me to get on with my own, as we<lb/>
                                        have no facility for getting money apart<lb/> from sales, as
                                        collections cannot be made</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">You will please charge me with the<lb/> Prayer
                                        Books as I cannot spare the amt<lb/> for them at the
                                        present. I fear <persName>Dia's</persName><lb/> Letters will
                                        not sell in <placeName>Atlanta</placeName>, as I<lb/> cannot
                                        induce any of our people to take<lb/> a copy, and of course
                                        those of the adverse<lb/> faith will not. I delivered your
                                        message<lb/> to <persName>Mr Mayer</persName>, and no doubt
                                        under the cir=<lb/>cumstances he will excuse you for
                                        not<lb/> replying. You will please excuse all errors<lb/> as
                                        I have no clerk and am obliged to have<lb/> the titles and
                                        wait upon all customers<lb/> who present themselves.
                                                  <persName>Mrs. A.</persName>
                                        <add>?</add>
                                        <persName>Mrs B.</persName><lb/> and all your friends unite
                                        in presenting<lb/> to you their kind regards, and with
                                        the<lb/> tender of my services in what ever way<lb/> you can
                                        make them available</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">I am yours Truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <persName role="author">A. Alexander</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>I have no time to write</p>
                              <p>and correct my letters</p>
                              <p>so take this for what</p>
                              <p>it may be worth</p>
                    </body>
